36
00:02:46,030 --> 00:02:50,629
practical-minded Dutch. Japan and Holland
were vastly different cultures, but each shared

37
00:02:50,629 --> 00:02:56,620
a timeless and universal concern: self-interest.
3. Don’t confuse your needs with others

38
00:02:56,620 --> 00:03:01,239
Once you make people see how you can in some
way meet their needs or advance their cause,

39
00:03:01,239 --> 00:03:05,430
their resistance to your requests for help
will magically fall away. At each step on

40
00:03:05,430 --> 00:03:09,469
the way to acquiring power, you must train
yourself to think your way inside the other

41
00:03:09,469 --> 00:03:14,128
person's mind, to see their needs and interests,
to get rid of the screen of your own feelings

42
00:03:14,128 --> 00:03:19,429
that obscure the truth. Master this art and
there will be no limits to what you can accomplish.

43
00:03:19,430 --> 00:03:23,939
